{{Infobox storm | name = | image = | alt = | caption = | formed = | active = | dissipated = | lowest pressure = | lowest temperature = | tornadoes = | fujitascale = F4 | tornado duration = | highest winds = | gusts = | maximum snow = | power outages = | total fatalities = | damages = | affected = | location = | current advisories = | enhanced = | notes = }} The '''1918 Tyler tornado''' was a large and destructive [[tornado]] that devastated the town of [[Tyler, Minnesota]] on Wednesday, August 21, 1918. The [[Fujita scale|F4]]-estimated tornado hit the town at approximately 9:20 pm, killing 36&nbsp;people and injuring over 100 others.<ref>[http://climate.umn.edu/doc/historical/tornadic.htm Minnesota Tornado History and Statistics<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070811154836/http://climate.umn.edu/doc/historical/tornadic.htm |date=2007-08-11 }}</ref><ref>[http://www3.gendisasters.com/minnesota/3395/tyler,-mn-tornado,-aug-1918 Tyler, MN Tornado, Aug 1918 | GenDisasters ... Genealogy in Tragedy, Disasters, Fires, Floods<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Debris from Tyler was found up to {{convert|23|mi|km|0}} away.<ref>[http://www.tylertribute.com/web%20page.htm Welcome To Tyler, Minnesota<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513063753/http://www.tylertribute.com/web%20page.htm |date=2008-05-13 }}</ref> It is the fourth-deadliest tornado in [[Minnesota]]'s history.
