{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}
'''Ananth Hegde Ashisara''' is an environmentalist from [[Uttara Kannada]] district, [[Karnataka]], [[India]] and Chairman, Western Ghats Task Force.

==Fight to protect Western Ghat==
Ashisara is involved in protection of environment, especially [[Western Ghats]], a [[World Heritage]] site and he is Chairman, Western Ghat Task Force.<ref name="deccan1">{{cite news | last =| first = | title =10 ancient trees named arboreal heritage  | newspaper =Deccan Herald (Bangalore) | date =4 August 2010 | url =http://www.deccanherald.com/content/86164/10-ancient-trees-named-arboreal.html |accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref> He is also convenor of ''Vriksh Laksha Andolan'', a group of people from [[Malenadu]] dedicated to protect environment.
He is involved in people's movement against mining activities in and around [[Ambaragudda]] hill range of Western Ghats located in [[Shimoga District]], Karnataka.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.thehindu.com/2005/08/17/stories/2005081702670300.htm|title = Andolan seeks restoration of ban on mining at Ambargudda|last = |first = |date = 17 August 2005|work = |access-date = 12 January 2015|publisher = Hindu}}</ref>

He has put efforts to get ''arboreal heritage'' tag to 10 old trees of Karnataka, which include Big Banyan tree, Bangalore (400 years old), ''Adansonia digitata'' - Malvaceae, Bijapur Taluk (600 years old), "Pilali" tree ''Ficus micro corpus'', [[Banavasi]], [[Uttara Kannada]] etc.<ref name=deccan1/> He expressed concern over safety of nuclear energy in the wake of damage experienced by [[nuclear power]] projects  in [[Japan]] [[tsunami]] (2010).<ref>{{cite news | last =Pinto  | first =Stanley | title =Task force concerned | newspaper =The Times of India | date = | url =http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Task-force-concerned/speednewsbytopic/keyid-592068.cms |accessdate=5 October 2012}}</ref>

