An '''avalanche boulder tongue''' is an accumulation of debris produced by [[snow]] [[avalanches]]. Well developed avalanche boulder tongue usually develop below [[avalanche gullie]]s due to successive avalanches over a long time span. The avalanche boulder tongues were first intensively investigated by [[Anders Rapp]] in the areas of [[Abisko]] and [[Kebnekaise]] in [[Swedish Lappland]].

