=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016123312/http://www.worldofwindenergy.com/vbnews.php?do=viewarticle&artid=455&title=french-wind-turbine-maker-eyes-projects-in-rp|archivedate=October 16, 2012|df=}}</ref> It is the second wind farm built in the province of [[Ilocos Norte]] and the largest project of its kind in the [[Philippines]]. The estimated cost for the construction of the wind farm was US$450&nbsp;million. The wind farm was commissioned in November 9, 2014 and upon its completion it became the largest wind farm in the country and in Southeast Asia, covering 600 hectares and three barangays of Burgos, namely Saoit, Poblacion and Nagsurot. The project was the first one to be nominated by the [[Department of Energy (Philippines)|Department of Energy]] as eligible for the department's [[feed-in tariff]] scheme.<ref name=int /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Gonzales|first1=Iris|title=SEA’s biggest wind farm powers Luzon|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/11/09/1389632/seas-biggest-wind-farm-powers-luzon|accessdate=November 9, 2014|work=Philippine Star|date=November 9, 2014}}</ref>
