'''Nisinic acid''' is a very long chain [[polyunsaturated fatty acid|polyunsaturated]] [[omega-3 fatty acid]], similar to [[docosahexaenoic acid]] (DHA).  The lipid name is 24:6 (n-3) and the chemical name is ''all''-''cis''-6,9,12,15,18,21-tetracosahexaenoic acid.  It is not well studied, but [[polyunsaturated fatty acid]]s even longer than DHA, nisinic acid included, may hold scientific promise.<ref>{{Cite book | chapter= Nisinic acid, 24: 6n-3, and other methylene-interrupted very long chain polyunsaturated fatty acids | date = 2011 | author = Vyssotski, M. | title= Lipids: Categories, Biological Functions and Metabolism, Nutrition and Health | editor = Paige L. Gilmore | pages = 199 - 216 | isbn = 9781616684648 | chapter-url= https://www.callaghaninnovation.govt.nz/nisinic-acid-24-6n-3-and-other-methylene-interrupted-very-long-chain-polyunsaturated-fatty-acids}}</ref>{{vague|date=February 2018}}

