'''''Terra Nova''''' is a Floating Production Storage and Offloading Vessel ([[FPSO]]) located in the [[Terra Nova (oil field)|Terra Nova]] [[oil and gas field]], approximately {{convert|350|km|mi|sp=us}} east-southeast off the coast of [[Newfoundland (island)|Newfoundland]], [[Canada]] in the [[North Atlantic Ocean]]. The Terra Nova field is operated by [[Suncor Energy Inc.]], with a 33.9% interest.

The Terra Nova field is south of the successful [[Hibernia (oil field)|Hibernia]] field and the more recent [[White Rose (oil field)|White Rose]] field. All three fields are in the [[Jeanne d'Arc Basin]] on the eastern edge of the famous [[Grand Banks]] fishing territory.

''Terra Nova'' lost 165,000 liters of oil into the ocean in 2004 because of two mechanical failures.  In June 2006, production on ''Terra Nova'' was halted as the platform was sent to [[Rotterdam]] for a refit. She returned to the Terra Nova field on 25 September 2006.

