'''Uno Bolt''' is a one-wheel electric self-balancing vehicle. It was first introduced to the public in August 2017 on Kickstarter. The company that manufactures the devie was founded by entrepreneur Sean Chan and is distributed by LED Impressions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unobolt.com|title=Uno Bolt|website=Uno Bolt|access-date=2017-08-22}}</ref> The product has been featured in publications such as Men's Journal, Business Insider, and Digital Trends.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mensjournal.com/gear/articles/now-you-can-own-a-fat-wheeled-electric-unicycle-just-like-james-cameron-w494678|title=Now You Can Own a Fat-Wheeled Electric Unicycle Just Like James Cameron|work=Men's Journal|access-date=2017-08-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/electric-unicycle-charges-45-minutes-go-22-mph-technology-transport-kickstarter-uno-bolt-2017-8|title=This electric unicycle charges in 45 minutes and can go 22 mph|work=Business Insider|access-date=2017-08-22|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/outdoors/uno-bolt-kickstarter/|title=Uno Bolt is a fat-wheeled electric unicycle with Gyro Force technology|date=2017-08-17|work=Digital Trends|access-date=2017-08-22|language=en-US}}</ref> Uno Bolt will be featured in [[James Cameron]]'s 2018 movie "Alita: Battle Angels".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mensjournal.com/gear/articles/now-you-can-own-a-fat-wheeled-electric-unicycle-just-like-james-cameron-w494678|title=Now You Can Own a Fat-Wheeled Electric Unicycle Just Like James Cameron|work=Men's Journal|access-date=2017-08-22}}</ref>
